               <p>On Wednesday the 25th of June, I was going through <placeName id="t17880625-72-crimeloc323">George lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17880625-72-crimeloc323" type="placeName" value="George lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17880625-72-crimeloc323" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17880625-72-off321 t17880625-72-crimeloc323"></join>, which leads into Botolph-lane, I felt something at my coat-pocket, I turned round and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand, he threw it down and ran away; I took it up, and a person in the lane stopped him, I charged a constable with him, and took him before an alderman.</p>
               <p>Was he ever out of your sight? - Never.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was coming down the lane, this gentleman laid hold of me, and said I had took his handkerchief, I know nothing of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17880625-72-verdict324" type="verdictDescription">
